<div class="nohero w-full">

    <!-- Hero: pattern from factory-efficiency -->
    <div class="w-full pt-12 pb-20 md:pt-6 md:pb-12">
        <div class="md:flex px-6 md:my-16 items-center md:flex-row md:justify-between container mx-auto text-center md:text-left md:max-w-screen-lg gap-8 items-stretch">

            <div class="m-auto md:w-1/2">
                <h1 class="w-full mt-0 px-6 md:px-0 m-auto font-medium">
                    <span class="text-4xl">Building industrial applications works <span class="text-indigo-600">until you need to scale them</span></span>
                </h1>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Most industrial teams start by solving a <span class="font-medium">single use case</span> —
                    connecting a machine, moving data, or building a workflow.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-10">
                    That's the right approach early on, the challenge appears when those
                    solutions need to <span class="font-medium">scale across sites, teams, and systems.</span>
                </p>
                <a class="ff-btn ff-btn--highlight hidden min-h-[40px] md:inline uppercase"
